        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 22 at 6:36PM EDT by NWS Raleigh NC</headline>
        <description>At 636 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Nashville, moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts in excess of 30 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Enfield, Leggett, Whitakers, Pinetops, Tarboro, Conetoe, Elm City,
Scotland Neck, Tar River Reservoir, and Princeville.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
